Pre-Game Insights: Our prediction for this Nations League match: Kosovo 1-0 Romania
Romania were one of just four European sides to take part at the first ever World Cup in 1930
Led by arguably their best ever footballer Gheorghe Hagi, the Tricolorii narrowly missed out on the semi-finals at the 1994 World Cup in the United States, losing to Sweden on penalties
Romania made a total of seven appearances at the World Cup finals, while qualifying for five European Championship tournaments
Romania play their home games at the Arena National in Bucarest
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Romanians, on the other hand, were producing fine performances at the EURO 2024, with the team making it to the last 16 of the showpiece tournament in Germany
The good news for the away team is that defender Vasile Mogos has overcome the injury he suffered in the EURO 2024 clash with Netherlands
